# JARVIS — environment variables example
#
# HOW TO USE:
#   1. Copy this file to a new file named exactly ".env" (no .example).
#   2. Put your real OpenRouter API key after the "=" below.
#   3. Save. The .env file is gitignored, so your key is never committed.
#
# WHERE TO GET A KEY:
#   Sign up (free tier available) at https://openrouter.ai/ and create an
#   API key. It looks like:  sk-or-v1-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
#
# Without this key the assistant still hears and speaks, but cannot give
# smart replies (the "brain" stays offline).

OPENROUTER_API_KEY=your-key-here
